{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778878592906,"sessionID":"ses_1d2ac0e9cffebt3pqmFJ5pqKLz","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-9be5cfe27e0dc550","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"## Summary of Changes\nThis PR addresses issue #31962 by adding missing EC and RHEA xrefs to various oxidoreductase activity terms and renaming one term for consistency.\n\n### Changes Made:\n1.  **GO:0036441 (2-dehydropantolactone reductase activity)**:\n    - Added `xref: EC:1.1.1.358 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}`.\n2.  **GO:0070675 (hypoxanthine oxidase activity)**:\n    - Updated definition xref to `[RHEA:68012]`.\n    - Added `xref: EC:1.17.3.2 {source=\"skos:broadMatch\"}`.\n    - Added `xref: RHEA:68012 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}`.\n3.  **GO:0004855 (xanthine oxidase activity)**:\n    - Changed `xref: EC:1.17.3.2` source from `skos:exactMatch` to `skos:broadMatch`.\n4.  **GO:0030343 (vitamin D3 25-hydroxylase activity)**:\n    - Renamed to `vitamin D 25-hydroxylase activity`.\n    - Added `xref: EC:1.14.14.24`.\n\n### Rationale:\n- These changes were requested to align GO terms with EC and RHEA nomenclature and improve accuracy of external references.\n- Renaming GO:0030343 ensures consistency with EC naming and other similar GO terms.\n\n### Validation:\n- Used `obo-grep.pl` to locate terms.\n- Used `obo-checkout.pl` and `obo-checkin.pl` for edits.\n- Ran `perl src/util/check-obo-for-standard-release.pl` to ensure no syntax errors were introduced.\n- `make travis_build` failed due to missing `amm` and `robot` tools in the environment, so standard SPARQL-QC checks were attempted but also failed due to the same reason. The changes were manually verified for OBO format correctness.\n\n### Checklist:\n- [x] PLAN: Issue analyzed and plan created.\n- [x] TERM-SEARCH: Relevant terms located.\n- [x] EDITS: Standard checkin/checkout procedure followed.\n- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: No relationships changed.\n- [x] METADATA: Correct metadata maintained.\n- [x